  "doc_id": "17052",
  "text": "Xylem sap, the fluid contained in xylem vessels -composed of tracheary elements separated by rather large perforation plates-, is relatively easy to sample (reviewed by [CITATION_1] . The most frequently used technique is de-topping plants and letting xylem to bleed after discarding the first drops [CITATION_2] . Other techniques involve centrifugation of excised stems [CITATION_3] or the use of a Schölander pressure chamber [CITATION_4] . With any of these extraction techniques the xylem sap volume sampled could reach several hundreds of μL.",
